  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">(i)	Health outcomes: The Hospital will be the first in Mongolia operated to international best practice and is expected to provide health services to over 100,000 patients. (ii)	Import substitution: The Hospital will provide services to patients in Mongolia who typically travel abroad for health care.  (iii)	Employment Creation: The Project is expected to create around 300 new job opportunities in Ulaanbaatar.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Intermed LLC is building and will operate the International Medical Center, an 80-bed greenfield general hospital in Ulaanbaatar, Mongolia. The hospital will be the first in Mongolia implemented to international best practice, incorporating Joint Commission International and World Health Organization universal patient safety and infection control standards. Main services will include an outpatient department; an inpatient department covering surgery, internal medicine, pediatrics, OB&amp;GY; emergency &amp; medical evacuation; and a health screening department. Hospital opening is expected in November 2013.</narrative>
  </description>
